text.tspan: Preventing Infections:
All day we're facing a multitude of pathogens like viruses and bacteria. Simple steps to proper hygiene
help to prevent yourself and others from infectious diseases.
10 Steps to Proper Hygiene
Wash hands regularly
once you arrive at home
before and during food preparation
before eating
after using the restroom
after wiping your nose, coughing, sneezing
before and after contact with sick people
after contact with animals
Don't touch your face
Refrain from touching your mouth, eyes,
or nose with unwashed hands.
Wash hands thouroughly
hold hands under flowing water
lather well from all sides
take your time! 20 to 30 seconds
rinse hands under flowing water
dry hands well using clean towel
Keep a distance when sick
Stay at home to get better. Refrain from
close bodily contacts. In cases of high risk
of infection, it might be advisable to stay
in a separate room and use separate
restrooms. Do not share personal items like
towels and drinking glasses.
Protect wounds
Cover lesions or wounds with a band-aid
or bandage.
Handle food hygienically
Keep perishable foods well refridgerated at
all times. Prevent contact between raw
animal products and foods eaten raw.
Heat meat to at least 70°C. Throughly wash
raw vegetables and fruits before eating.
Cough and sneeze correctly
Best cough or sneeze into a hankerchief or
hold the crook of your arm in front of mouth
and nose while keeping your distance and
turning away from people near you.
Wash up using hot water
Clean kitchen utensils with warm water and
detergent or using a washing machine set to
at least 60°C. Wash rags as well as towels,
bed covers and underwear at least at 60°C.
Keep a clean home
Take specific care in cleaning restroom
and kitchen using common cleaning agents.
Dry cleaning rags well and replace them
often.
Ventilate periodically
Ventilate closed rooms multiple times daily
by fully opening all windows for a few minutes.
